description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medicines Management Directorate has an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and committed registered pharmacy technician to join our pharmacy team based at the Princess of Wales Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main duties will include Inpatient, Outpatient and Discharge Dispensing both within our pharmacy department and at ward level. We are committed to the development of the technician role and you will have the opportunity to attain both the accredited checking technician qualification and Medicines Management qualification .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must possess excellent communication and organisational skills in order to provide an efficient and safe pharmacy service for the patients of Bridgend and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have a BTEC and NVQ Level 3 In Pharmaceutical Sciences Or Equivalent and be registered with the General Pharmaceutical Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sarah Leyshon Job title Chief Pharmacy Technician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address sarah.leyshon@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01656 752382&lt;/p&gt;
